Package: mes
Type: Package
Title: Mixed Exponential Smoothing
Version: 1.1.1
Authors@R: person("Ivan", "Svetunkov", email = "ivan@svetunkov.ru", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  comment="Lecturer at Centre for Marketing Analytics and Forecasting, Lancaster University, UK")
URL: https://github.com/config-i1/mes
BugReports: https://github.com/config-i1/mes/issues
Language: en-GB
Description: The functions in the package are based on the Single Source of Error state space model
             by Hyndman et al., (2008, <doi: 10.1007/978-3-540-71918-2>). They make the framework more general,
             encompassing the classical ETS as a special case of the MESS model. This allows taking the multiple
             frequencies in the data into account (including the fractional frequencies), treating missing values
             and dealing with intermittent data (Svetunkov & Boylan, 2017, <doi: 10.13140/RG.2.2.35897.06242>).
